Investcorp, the Bahrain asset
manager that owns stakes in Gucci and Saks Fifth Avenue, said it
raised $793 million for new investments in the second half, the
most since the start of the financial crisis in 2008.  The firm amassed $516 million from institutional investors
for hedge funds, $204 million in corporate investment, and $73
million for real estate, it said today in an e-mailed statement.
The Manama-based firm said it returned $1.1 billion from
investment realizations and distributions to itself and clients.  Investcorp has investments in Gucci and Saks Fifth Avenue,
and about $11.5 billion in assets under management, according to
its website. Earlier this month the firm it sold CCC Information
Services Inc. to private equity firm Leonard Green and Partners
LP for more than $550 million.  The investment company also said today profit rose to $39.2
million in the six months ended Dec. 31, from $5.2 million in
the year-earlier period.  To contact the reporters on this story:
